[Only 0.7% of patients who had severe COVID-19 infections contract the disease "a 2nd time, with a mean reinfection period of 116 days," according to researchers who "analyzed data from more than 9100 COVID-19 patients at 62 health facilities in the United States." The article adds, "Non-white patients had a higher risk of reinfection than white patients" (from Qureshi et al., cited above). - Mod.LK]

