[3C] Nepal
Date: Wed 16 Jun 2021 05:05 p.m. NPT
Source: The Himalayan Times [abridged, edited]
https://thehimalayantimes.com/nepal/nepals-daily-covid-19-recoveries-continue-to-outnumber-new-cases


Nepal's coronavirus caseload reached 614 216 on [Wed 16 Jun 2021] with 2014 more people testing positive for the infection in the past 24 hours.

The highest single-day total logged in Nepal was on [11 May 2021], where 9317 infections were logged.

Meanwhile, the total coronavirus recoveries stand at 543 521 with 3082 discharges recorded today [16 Jun 2021].

In the past 24 hours, 52 more COVID-related fatalities were logged, taking the total death toll to 8558.

As per the latest data provided by the health ministry, 13 022 total tests were conducted in the last 24 hours, of which 8687 were PCR tests while 4335 were antigen tests. With this, a total of 3 240 299 PCR tests have been carried out till date [16 Jun 2021].

Similarly, antigen tests have confirmed 814 positive cases in the past 24 hours. The total number of single-day infections from both the RT-PCR and antigen tests add up to 2828.

Nepal's COVID-19 recovery rate stands at 88.5% on [Wed 16 Jun 2021], while, on the other hand, the fatality rate stands at 1.6%.

The country's active COVID-19 case count has dropped to 62 117 with daily recoveries exceeding daily infections.

In the same time frame, 354 infections were reported in the capital city while Lalitpur and Bhaktapur reported 66 and 79 cases, respectively.

So far, a total of 3 153 419 people have received coronavirus vaccine across the country, of which 2 461 925 have received the 1st dose while only 691 494 individuals have been inoculated with both the doses and are fully vaccinated.

On [Tue 15 Jun 2021], Nepal's coronavirus case count had reached 612 202 with 1681 more people testing positive for the infection.

