[3D] Pakistan
Date: Fri 18 Jun 2021
Source: Dawn [edited]
https://www.dawn.com/news/1629954/number-of-covid-cases-falls-by-65pc-in-two-months


The number of active cases of COVID-19 in the country has declined by 65% in about 2 months, and positivity rate continues to hover around 3% for the last 2 weeks, according to data shared by the National Command and Operation Centre (NCOC).

The number of patients admitted to hospitals, which was around 7000 in [April 2021], was 2746 as of [17 Jun 2021]. Meanwhile, 1119 cases and 46 deaths were reported in a single day with positivity rate of 3.01%.

During the previous 2 waves of the pandemic, the country hit the figure of 50 000 active cases, and then the number of cases started decreasing.

During the 1st wave of the pandemic, number of active cases surpassed the figure of 50 000 in June 2020, but later it started decreasing and finally dropped to less than 6000 in September last year [2020].

The number of cases again started rising in October 2020, due to which the NCOC declared it 2nd wave of infections, and the number of active cases surpassed the figure of 50 000 in December [2020].

Then again the number of active cases started decreasing and reached around 16 000 in February 2021. Again, the number of cases started increasing, due to which 3rd wave of infections was declared, and number of cases surpassed the figure of 50 000 for the 3rd time on [31 Mar 2021]. The number continued increasing and surpassed the figure of 90 000 in April [2021].

In the last week of April [2021], the NCOC decided to seek the help of the Pakistan Army to ensure the implementation of Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs) to curb the spread of coronavirus.

The provinces and the administrative units sought help of armed forces for implementation of the SOPs. Because of the move, implementation of the SOPs was improved. Moreover, lockdown was announced from [8 May 2021] due to which number of cases declined.

According to the NCOC data, the number of active cases across the country was 36 215 as of 17 Jun 2021]. The number was around 65% less as compared to April this year [2021] when the number of active cases was over 90 000.

The data further showed that 282 ventilators were in use of COVID-19 patients across the country.

[Byline: Ikram Junaidi]

